The paper discusses the use of fog computing and artificial intelligence for content-centric networking in 5G, which involves networking, distributed computing, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a framework for edge learning, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses the use of statistics and simulations, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobility control and traffic offloading, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
